text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!MorphosyntacticDiversity]]%0a%0a!Null or Zero Copula in African American English%0a%0a:Author: khushiw%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aThe grammatical exclusion of "to be" verbs in African American English%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aAfrican American Language (AAL) has a unique grammatical construction that involves the dropping of "to be" verbs. Commonly, this is called Null Copula or Zero Copula. This is apparent in common sentences from AAL/AAVE such as "she runnin'" or "she home yesterday". Although seemingly random, this grammatical construction follows a very clear set of rules:%0a%0a1. copula cannot be omitted if unstressed%0a2. copula cannot be omitted at the end of a phrase%0a3. copula cannot be omitted for first-person subjects%0a4. copula cannot be omitted when negated%0a5. copula cannot be omitted in its infinitive form "to be"%0a6. copula cannot be omitted in the past tense%0a7. copula cannot be omitted in the AAVE remote present perfect (not in standard English)%0a8. copula cannot be omitted in a confirmatory tag question%0a%0aThe omission of a copula is present in many different languages beyond English. AAL/AAVE is a dialect of English in which it is very prevalent.%0a%0aSources: https://ygdp.yale.edu/african-american-language-and-grammatical-diversity-2020#grammar-and-systematicity%0ahttp://www.ling.ohio-state.edu/~nvail/202/SP03/materials/aave.txt%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: B:)%0a(:Category: MorphosyntacticDiversity:)
